ml-hard-h1,H,hard-h,16200,11700,21600,49500,balanced,602,budget,yes,537,0.89,no,yes,no,23,3,39,minor,"Largest memory (3x) + hardest non-palindromic question sustained genuine math longest (~0.8 of run: proved 65 unique 2-digit, no 3- or 4-digit solutions) with many closure-recoveries, but drifted to an easier sums-of-two-squares variant, lost the origin framing, then a kaleidoscope-hallucination closure at burst 537/602 collapsed it into a deep beautiful-thing/leave-it-there presence loop; 3 transient consolidation failures bloated memory.md"
